{
  "texts": [
    "The attention mechanism (Bahdanau et al. 2014 (Bahdanau et al., 2014)) is an architecture that assigns a weight to each hidden state representation of an input sequence in order to determine which part of the input to focus on.",
    "One advantage of the attention mechanism is its ability to parallelize computations, as it does not rely on the sequence order.",
    "This mechanism has become a core component of transformer models.",
    "where α i and v i are attention weights and representation of the input (hidden states from lower layers), respectively.",
    "W u represents the weight vectors and m i represents the atten- tion vectors for the i-th word, and h i is the final representation of weighted sum of all the word vectors.Integrating attention mechanisms with CNN and LSTM has emerged as a popular approach in various research studies (Taghipour and Ng 2016; Dong et al. 2017; He et al. 2022)."
  ]
}